From: New homes of Army men's families on Milstead Avenue, about five miles outside of Columbus, Georgia. They were built this past September, to What say teachers? "A howling success" At Milstead, Ga., a class in Home Hygiene and Care of the Sick composed entirely of teachers recently completed the course. Upon being asked for an expression regarding its value, Miss Eloise Kerlin, one of the teachers, expressed her sentiments by a hand made poster inscribed, "A howling success," a reproduction of which accompanies this article.
